Recommended Missing Core Tools
These are standard drawing app tools that are absent from the current build. Ranked by value-to-effort for the TestFlight window.
High Value / Low Effort

Opacity slider — per-layer opacity control in the layers panel. Essential for layered workflows. Slider 0–100% that feeds into the compositor.
Straight line with snap — a dedicated line tool that snaps to 45° increments when a second finger touches the screen (same Procreate-style multitouch pattern as the square/circle snap). Different from the current line tool which doesn't snap.

High Value / Medium Effort

Layer blend modes — Normal, Multiply, Screen, Overlay at minimum. Applied per-layer in the compositor. Massive boost to what users can create without adding new tools.
Crop tool — define a region and crop the canvas to it. Useful for export. No new render pipeline needed, just adjust the export region.

Medium Value / Low Effort

Flip horizontal / Flip vertical — canvas-level transforms. Common action, trivial to implement via a texture flip in the renderer.
Symmetry / mirror mode — mirror strokes across a vertical or horizontal axis in real time. Popular for portrait and mandala drawing. Medium complexity but high delight factor for the target user.

