Architecture Notes
Critical — do not touch without reading
Coordinate Pipeline (load-bearing)
screenToDocument / documentToScreen / quadVertexShaderWithTransform must stay in sync at all times. Any change to one requires retest of all three on physical iPad. This was the source of Phase 1's major bugs and must not regress.

Canvas texture: 4096×4096 (sized from view.drawableSize, not view.bounds.size)
fitSize model: uses max(viewport.w, viewport.h) — fill, not fit
Rotation convention: shader Y-up (visual CCW), Swift R(-theta) for Y-down equivalent
Marquee selection: stored as 4-point screen-space polygon mapped to doc space via screenToDocument. Routes through lasso pipeline. activeSelection is nil for all marquee selections — selectionPath is ground truth.

Memory

4096×4096 × 4 bytes = 64MB per layer
5 layers = 320MB — monitor on base iPad, fine on iPad Pro
History manager caps at 50 snapshots — each snapshot is 64MB; limit is effectively the memory ceiling, not the count

Worker Auth

No auth, no rate limiting, CORS wide open — acceptable for TestFlight, must address before public launch
API key lives in Cloudflare Worker environment variable OPENAI_API_KEY
Deploy via wrangler deploy from cloudflare-worker/ with CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN set


